{
  "texts": [
    "In this figure, one can easily verify that the depth is O(m).",
    "Finally, in Algorithm 5, we give pseudocode for the implementation of SPF, consistent with the labels appearing in Fig. 16.",
    "To understand the idea behind the circuits, we now describe several rules that must be obeyed (and the reasoning why):1.j (D q) needs to happen after i (D q) if j < i, ∀q:• This is true by construction, shown in Fig. 12.",
    "2.j (D q) needs to happen after SWAP(D q,0, A q,0), ∀j, ∀q:• This is because the injection of the angle state into data qubit q must occur before we can begin to copy data qubit q.3.",
    "CS k (D q, •) needs to happen after k-1 (D q), ∀q:• This makes sure we can have enough qubits for the CSWAP sequence to control on in order to guarantee maximal parallelization.4."
  ]
}